title: Complete coverage: Colonial League girls cross country championship
text:
Complete Box Score » 
New and old each had their turn at the top of Wednesday’s Colonial League girls cross country championship at DeSales University in Center Valley. 
The new came from Saucon Valley freshman Kiele Riefenstahl , who won the individual title in 19 minutes and 46 seconds. 
The old came from Northwestern Lehigh, which won its fifth consecutive team championship. 
Follow the links below for complete coverage of the meet.
